copy.tutorial_txt_01: Welcome to Sunflower Gully, sunshine! We need to collect all kinds of light to make rainbows on the mainland!
copy.tutorial_txt_02: To collect light, move the oval mirrors around so the beams of light shine on the flower petal cups and fill them up!
copy.tutorial_txt_03: Easy, see? We used the mirror to reflect the light into the light cups!
copy.tutorial_txt_04: Move the mirrors around by dragging them to where you want.
copy.tutorial_txt_06: Here's a hint -- you can bounce light off more than one mirror to make it go around corners!
copy.tutorial_txt_07: Sometimes there is more than one light cup to fill up. No problem -- we've got special "Light Splitters" that split light into two beams!
copy.tutorial_txt_07b: Remember, all cups must be filled with the correct light color at the same time to finish the level!
copy.tutorial_txt_08: See how I used the splitter to fill both cups? Pretty clever, huh?
copy.tutorial_txt_09: That's it! Just keep an eye out for other things you can use to change the direction and color of the light.
copy.tutorial_txt_10: Check your score here, okay? And this shows you how many cups you need to fill.
copy.tutorial_txt_11: I'll be here with you the whole time if you need me!
copy.instruction0: To collect light, move the oval mirrors around so the beams of light shine on the flower petal cups and fill them up.
copy.instruction1: You can bounce light off more than one mirror to make the light go around corners!
copy.instruction2: Use gems to change the color of the light.
copy.instruction3: Sometimes there is more than one light cup to fill. Use a "Light Splitter" to split light into more than one beam!
copy.instruction4: Fill all the cups with the right color light at the same time to finish the level!
copy.game_over_win_0: You did it, sunshine! The mainland will have plenty of rainbows next season, thanks to you!

copy.level_tip_1: Move the mirror into the light to make it bend. Point the light at the flower cups to catch the light!
copy.level_tip_2: Shimmerific! Use more mirrors to make light bend around corners!
copy.level_tip_5: Colored “Gems” will turn the white light a different color. The color of the light has to match the color of the flower cup in order to fill it up.
copy.level_tip_6: “Light Splitters” will split the light into multiple beams. You can fill two cups at the same time, sunshine!
copy.level_tip_7: Light Splitters will even split colored light! Use them to fill two cups at the same time.
copy.level_tip_8: Use the “Light Splitter” to fill two cups at the same time.
copy.level_tip_10: Use “Cross Pieces” to split the light up into three beams! They're so helpful and fun.
copy.level_tip_11: Using Cross Pieces and Splitters together can help you fill lots of cups!
copy.level_tip_14: The “Rainbow Gem” not only splits the light, but it also changes it to three different colors at once!
copy.level_tip_23: Keep an eye on your Rainbow Gems. The white side isn't always on top!
copy.level_tip_26: Now there are multiple light sources. Use them both to solve the puzzle, moonbeam!
